Package easygraph

Interface Graph<T>

Type Parameters:
T - the type of the data of the vertices.
All Superinterfaces:
Serializable
All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractGraph, UndirectedGraph
public interface Graph<T> extends Serializable
A graph is a data structure that consists of the following two components: 1. A finite set of vertices also called as nodes. 2. A finite set of a pair of the form (u, v) called as edge.
